---
import "../styles/global.css"
import Shell from "../components/Shell.astro"
---

<Shell>
	<h1 class="mx-auto w-fit text-4xl underline -underline-offset-10 italic block decoration-4 font-['Minecraftia']">
		Welcome To My WebZone!
	</h1>

	<article class="mt-4 text-xl flex flex-col gap-y-8">
		<div class="*:mb-2 [&>*:last-child]:mb-0">
			<img src="/img/amandaprofile.png" width="500" height="500" alt="A pseudo-profile picture of Amanda O'Neil for the anime 'Little Witch Acedemia'." class="float-left w-60 max-w-1/3 h-fit mr-6 mb-2 border-2">
			<h2 class="text-3xl">
				My name is
				<span id="name" class="font-semibold">Addie!</span>
			</h2>
			<p>
				I'm a tech enthusiast and software/systems engineer.
			</p>
			<p>
				I've just graduated from the University of Kansas and am doing
				a technical internship with a tax preparation company.
			</p>
			<p>
				Outside of computer science and software engineering,
				I enjoy board games, anime, recreational cycling, and
				<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Construction_and_management_simulation" target="_blank" class="underline hover:text-theme-green">
					management simulation video games
				</a>.
			</p>
		</div>

		<p>
			My primary software interest areas are in full-stack web development and writing secure software.
			To this end, my favorite language is TypeScript - primarily for its wide use in the web domain,
			expansive package ecosystem,
			its expressive yet strict typing system, and its emphasis on static analysis.
			That said, I also enjoy writing in other languages including C++, C#, and Java.
		</p>

		<p>
			This website is intended as place for everything me!
			You should see a list of links on the sidebar - I encourage you to explore them.
			Right now, there might not be a whole lot there, but I plan to add sections as they become pertinent.
			My previous website had been around since I was in middle school and was in dire need of replacement.
			Hopefully, this site fares better and stands the test of time.
		</p>

		<p>
			Hope you enjoy your stay here!
		</p>
	</article>
</Shell>